In Gold Star Studios and the “Wall of Sound”

Once Brian Wilson heard Spector’s records, the Beach Boys’ composer-producer made many of his group’s records at Gold Star, and the rest of the industry followed, vainly hoping to capture that magic sound by using the same ingredients.

In surf music

…Beach Boys, however, led by Brian Wilson, whose complex vocal harmonies, skilled musicianship, inventive production, and evocative lyrics apotheosized surf music and culture with a remarkable string of hits such as “Surfin’ U.S.A.” (1963) and “California Girls” (1965).
